    <text>
        <body>
            <div>
                <opener><salute>Dear Sir</salute> <dateline><placeName ref="pl0001">Downing</placeName> Dec<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> 24<hi rend="superscript">th</hi>. 1797.</dateline></opener>
                <p>Excuse a short letter to say that I send by this evenings <placeName ref="pl0002">Chester</placeName> mail, the most material deficiency to y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>
                    copy of the <bibl type="authorial"><title ref="bi0023">arctic Zoology</title></bibl>. As to the two title pages, I am sorry to trouble you with directions about them, vide the inclosed<note type="editorial">This is not present with the manuscript letter.</note> for not being on the spot I cannot assist more than by instruction. Be so good as to order the size of the paper &amp; order a copy of the 2 title pages to be kept for me, because my copies are equally deficient. This bring on 
                    anticipation of the good wishes of the season by a single day. Let me request <persName ref="pe0331">miss Bull</persName> &amp; you to accept them with all sincerity from y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>
                    grateful friend. accept also duplicates of <rs type="art" ref="ar0450">eight picturesque drawings taken in the Bay of Fundy or its neighborhood</rs>. I fell on them by accident in searching after materials for my pastiferous operations. They were copied fr<hi rend="superscript">m</hi>
                    <bibl type="authorial"><title ref="bi0654">M. de Barres</title></bibl>'s <add place="above">see p. CCCXI</add> magnificent labors which I borrowed from the admiralty several years ago.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Adieu
                        <lb/>Dear Sir,
                        <lb/>ever &amp; affec<hi rend="superscript">tly</hi> yours</salute>
                    <signed><persName ref="pe0232">Tho. Pennant.</persName></signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Could you procure me the <del><gap unit="letters" quantity="1"/></del> oct<hi rend="superscript">vo</hi> <rs type="art" ref="ar0352">head of Sir Fr. Drake</rs>, 
                        &amp; of <rs type="art" ref="ar0353">Sir Humphrey Gilbert</rs> p CCCIII.</p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
